Azure Mobile Apps provide backend services for mobile applications, including authentication, data storage, and push notifications.

They integrate easily with iOS, Android, and cross-platform frameworks.

For example, a mobile app can use Azure Mobile Apps for user authentication and syncing data.

A real-life use case is a fitness app storing user activity data in the cloud.

Another example is a messaging app sending push notifications to users.

Mobile Apps backend simplifies mobile development and ensures scalability.
